orkspace/src/routes/activity.ts`\n\nThe activity endpoint returns all matching entries with no limit. As the activity log grows, this could return very large responses.\n\n**Recommendation:** Add `limit` and `offset` query parameters with sensible defaults (e.g., limit 50).\n\n---\n\n### Suggestions (Nice to Have)\n\n#### 10. `createApp` export verification\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/app.ts`, line 9\n\n`createApp` is properly exported as a named export: `export function createApp()`. The test file imports it correctly at `/workspace/src/app.test.ts`, line 3: `import { createApp } from './app.js'`. This is correct.\n\nHowever, there is no default export or `main` entry point to actually start the server. If this application needs to be run standalone (not just tested), a `main.ts` or an `if (import.meta.main)` block would be needed.\n\n#### 11. Register endpoint does not return password in the response -- VERIFIED CORRECT\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/routes/auth.ts`, line 34\n\nThe registration response correctly returns only `{ id, username }` and does not include the password. The test at `/workspace/src/app.test.ts` line 65 correctly asserts `expect(res.body.password).toBeUndefined()`. This requirement is satisfied.\n\n#### 12. Token is a simple UUID without expiration\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/routes/auth.ts`, line 59\n\nTokens are generated via `crypto.randomUUID()` and never expire. There is also no logout endpoint. A user who obtains a token has permanent access until the server restarts.\n\n#### 13. No validation that `content` is a string in document creation\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/routes/documents.ts`, lines 21-24\n\nThe code checks that `content` is not `undefined` or `null`, then coerces it with `String(content)` on line 48. This means a numeric or boolean content value would be silently converted to a string like `\"42\"` or `\"true\"`. Consider adding a type check:\n\n```typescript\nif (typeof content !== 'string') {\n  res.status(400).json({